<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-3467] PDPage.getAnnotations() modifies the PDF</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3467</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I stumbled across this bug while using PDFDebugger.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PDPage.getAnnotations() writes to the Page&apos;s COSDictionary, adding a new Annots entry if it is missing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This violates one of the rules which we introduced for 2.0, that reading from a PDF file should not result in the file&apos;s COS model being modified.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12998047">PDFBOX-3467</key>
            <summary>PDPage.getAnnotations() modifies the PDF</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
