                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15425543" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2016 22:51:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I fixed this in &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1756692&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc?view=revision&amp;amp;revision=1756692&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15425545" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 17 Aug 2016 22:54:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that this isn&apos;t a breaking change from an API point of view, but semantically it is. I think we&apos;re ok to ship this in 2.1 but I would not want to ship it in 2.0.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve used an unmodifiable list to make sure that anyone trying to modify the returned list in the empty-case will get an exception rather than a silent failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wish we&apos;d caught this in 2.0 but I think this change is better late than never.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15426014" author="tilman" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 07:13:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This last change (besides breaking several tests) means that if an empty list is returned, it cannot be modified (unless the empty list was there before), but if a non empty list is returned, it can be modified. So a user would now have to create an empty list if an empty list was returned and do what the three removed lines did.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;annots = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; COSArray();
page.setItem(COSName.ANNOTS, annots);
retval = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; COSArrayList&amp;lt;PDAnnotation&amp;gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ArrayList&amp;lt;PDAnnotation&amp;gt;(), annots);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15426575" author="tilman" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 14:57:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a possible solution after having a look at COSArrayList. Create a new constructor there:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;    /**
     * This constructor is to be used &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; the array doesn&apos;t exist, but is to be created and added to
     * the parent dictionary as soon as the first element is added to the array.
     *
     * @param dictionary The dictionary that holds the item, and will hold the array &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; an item is
     * added.
     * @param dictionaryKey The key into the dictionary to set the item.
     */
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; COSArrayList(COSDictionary dictionary, COSName dictionaryKey)
    {
        array = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; COSArray();
        actual = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ArrayList&amp;lt;E&amp;gt;();
        parentDict = dictionary;
        dictKey = dictionaryKey;
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;then the code you changed could be this instead:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; COSArrayList&amp;lt;PDAnnotation&amp;gt;(page, COSName.ANNOTS);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;in the add() method, COSArrayList would call setItem(), but only the first time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15426805" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 16:58:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, sorry I was absent-mindedly running with &lt;tt&gt;-D skipTests&lt;/tt&gt; set!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15426811" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 16:58:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fantastic. That&apos;s exactly the behaviour we want. This can go in 2.0 as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15426816" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 18 Aug 2016 17:04:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1756834 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1756834&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1756834&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

